  <!-- HTML Section -->
  <div class="section active" id="html">
    <h2>1. HTML — The Skeleton of Every Website</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <b>What is HTML?</b><br>
      <b>HTML</b> stands for <b>H</b>yper<b>T</b>ext <b>M</b>arkup <b>L</b>anguage.<br>
      It gives structure to your page: headings, text, links, images, lists, forms, etc.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> What tags make text <b>heading</b>?<br>
      <b>Q:</b> How do you make a clickable link?
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Basic Page Structure:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;My Page&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;This is my first web page.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <ul>
        <li><code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>: Headings (h1 is biggest)</li>
        <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code>: Paragraph (normal text)</li>
        <li><code>&lt;a href="..."&gt;</code>: Link</li>
        <li><code>&lt;img src="..."&gt;</code>: Image</li>
        <li><code>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;</code>: List</li>
        <li><code>&lt;input&gt;, &lt;form&gt;</code>: Forms</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: "About Me" Page</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;About Me&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;My Name is [Your Name]&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;I am from Angul, Odisha.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Coding&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Music&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Games&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.w3schools.com/"&gt;Learn More&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
      </div>
      <b>Try changing:</b> Your name, hobbies, add a photo, or more links!
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Practice:</b> Add a heading about your favorite food, and a link to a food recipe.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">HTML Forms Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;form&gt;
  Name: &lt;input type="text" name="name"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  <br>Email: &lt;input type="email" name="email"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  <br>&lt;button type="submit"&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> is used to get user data, like name or email.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CSS Section -->
  <div class="section" id="css">
    <h2>2. CSS — Make Your Page Beautiful</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <b>What is CSS?</b><br>
      <b>CSS</b> = <b>C</b>ascading <b>S</b>tyle <b>S</b>heets.<br>
      It adds color, layout, and style to your HTML.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> How do you change background or text color?<br>
      <b>Q:</b> What does <code>font-size</code> do?
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Simple CSS Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;style&gt;
  body { background: #f0f8ff; }
  h1 { color: #6c63ff; font-size: 38px; }
  p { color: #444; font-size: 20px; }
&lt;/style&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      Add this inside <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> in your HTML file.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Change Button Style:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
button {
  background: #6c63ff;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 7px 22px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
button:hover {
  background: #4834d4;
}
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Style your "About Me" page!</b>
      <ul>
        <li>Add a background color.</li>
        <li>Change h1 color and size.</li>
        <li>Add padding and border to your photo or paragraphs.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;style&gt;
  body { background: #fffbe4; }
  h1 { color: #d7263d; font-size: 36px; }
  p { color: #222; font-size: 22px; }
&lt;/style&gt;
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Practice:</b> Make one paragraph blue. Make your heading bigger. Give your list a border.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">CSS Box Model (Padding, Border, Margin):</div>
    <div class="code-block">
.box {
  background: #eaf2ff;
  padding: 12px;
  border: 2px solid #6c63ff;
  margin: 20px;
}
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <ul>
        <li><b>padding</b>: space inside the box</li>
        <li><b>border</b>: the edge</li>
        <li><b>margin</b>: space outside the box</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- JS Section -->
  <div class="section" id="js">
    <h2>3. JavaScript — Make Your Page Interactive</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <b>What is JavaScript?</b><br>
      <b>JavaScript (JS)</b> makes your webpage interactive: buttons, popups, animations, etc.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> How do you show an alert message when you click a button?
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Basic JS Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;button onclick="alert('Hello!')"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <code>alert(...)</code> shows a popup message.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Change Text with Button:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;h2 id="msg"&gt;Welcome!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('msg').innerText = 'You clicked me!';"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <ul>
        <li><code>id="msg"</code>: gives the heading a name</li>
        <li><code>onclick="..."</code>: runs JS code when button is clicked</li>
        <li><code>innerText</code>: changes the text</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">JS Variables and Math:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;script&gt;
  let a = 5;
  let b = 3;
  document.write("Sum: " + (a + b));
&lt;/script&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Practice:</b> Change <code>a</code> and <code>b</code>. Try <code>-</code>, <code>*</code>, <code>/</code> for math.
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Color Changer</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;button onclick="document.body.style.backgroundColor = 'yellow';"&gt;Yellow&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button onclick="document.body.style.backgroundColor = 'lightblue';"&gt;Blue&lt;/button&gt;
      </div>
      <b>Try:</b> Click buttons to change background color!
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Show/Hide Text Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;p id="showme" style="display:none;"&gt;Hello, I am webTune1!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('showme').style.display='block';"&gt;Show Name&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('showme').style.display='none';"&gt;Hide Name&lt;/button&gt;
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <code>style.display</code> shows/hides elements.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Challenge:</b> Make a button that increases a number each time you click.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">JS Functions Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
&lt;script&gt;
function greet(name) {
  alert('Hello, ' + name + '!');
}
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;button onclick="greet('webTune1')"&gt;Say Hi&lt;/button&gt;
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Python Section -->
  <div class="section" id="python">
    <h2>4. Python — Code For Everything</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <b>What is Python?</b><br>
      <b>Python</b> is a powerful, easy programming language for everything: scripts, games, data, automation, web, AI, and more.
      <br>You cannot run Python in your browser, but you can install it on your computer (see Resources).
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Basic Python Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
print("Hello, Python world!")
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <code>print(...)</code> shows a message in your terminal.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Variables and Math:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
a = 10
b = 5
print("Sum:", a + b)
print("Product:", a * b)
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">If-Else (Conditions):</div>
    <div class="code-block">
score = 56
if score >= 50:
    print("Pass")
else:
    print("Fail")
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Loops:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
for i in range(1, 6):
    print(i)
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">List Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
fruits = ["apple", "banana", "mango"]
for fruit in fruits:
    print(fruit)
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">Function Example:</div>
    <div class="code-block">
def greet(name):
    print("Hello,", name)

greet("webTune1")
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Python Calculator (Add, Subtract, Multiply, Divide)</b>
      <div class="code-block">
num1 = 7
num2 = 3

print("Sum:", num1 + num2)
print("Difference:", num1 - num2)
print("Product:", num1 * num2)
print("Quotient:", num1 / num2)
      </div>
      <b>Try:</b> Change numbers and see the result.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Practice:</b> Write a Python program to print your name and your favorite food.
    </div>
    <div class="mini-title">How to run Python:</div>
    <ul>
      <li>Install Python: <a href="https://www.python.org/" target="_blank">python.org</a></li>
      <li>Write code in Notepad/VS Code. Save as <b>test.py</b></li>
      <li>Open Command Prompt, type: <code>python test.py</code></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

